snippet.textDisplay:
I wonder something about all these dislikes. Is it just because it's an FE character? Because it's a swordfighter (or at least, a heavy user of disjoints?). I can understand some of the negative reactions, like how the DLC were going strong with 3rd parties until Byleth, or how Fire Emblem is now one of the more represented franchises despite carrying less weight than the likes of Mario, Kirby, or Pokémon.

This exact same thing happened with Corrin in Smash 4. A sword-using FE character was added by Nintendo to promote upcoming FE content (Assuming Byleth is here to promote the Three Houses DLC), and despite the character challenging the FE status quo of "Marth Clone", they are hated for simply being there. Some of the dislikes may be from these same people.

Another thing, now that the negative reactions are becoming widely covered on news sites, YouTube, and probably within social circles (such as Discord servers), it may have become "trendy" to dislike Byleth's appearance in Smash. People of either neutral or indifferent opinion may have disliked simply to hop onto the bandwagon, skewing the perception of the character and therefore attracting more bandwagoneers.

Then there is what I call "valid hate". This covers the dislikes from people who are genuinely unhappy with the character in Smash (either because of their visual appearance, moveset, or playstyle), people who do not like the character from the home game, and people who were expecting somebody else and ended up disappointed (like those who wanted Dante).

Now I like the idea of Byleth being in Smash, even though I would have preferred Dante by a long shot. Just to reduce bias, I reckon the likes on the video fall into similar, yet opposite, categories - people who are liking simply to oppose the dislikes, people who are liking because they like the idea of the character either in Smash or from their home game, and people who wanted the character.

This is totally open to discussion, as long as it remains civil.

snippet.textDisplay: I'm not too upset about this inclusion I mean if I hated Byleth then I probably wouldn't be a Dimileth shipper, but it probably wasn't the right time to reveal Byleth or at the very least have Byleth be the last character of the first fighters pass, Byleth probably should have been the character to start the next fighters pass to show that 1st and 2nd party Nintendo characters have a chance to be DLC as much as 3rd party ones do, or if Byleth had to be introduced at this time they probably should have done what they did at the E3 2019 Nintendo Direct, and had a double reveal like they did with Hero and Banjo-Kazooie, by having Byleth be the first reveal and then showed off at the very least a tease of the first DLC fighter for the next fighters pass at the end of the Byleth announcement, I can guarantee that a lot less people would be upset over Byleth if there had been a reveal of at least one of the next characters from the 2nd fighters pass at least being shown off along with Byleth, and no I'm not someone who hates Byleth as I said if I did I wouldn't be someone who ships Dimileth if I did, I'm just saying that there would probably be less people upset if Byleth wasn't the only character shown off and that we at least got shown a character off from the 2nd fighters pass, I mean even just a non-gameplay trailer of a character from the 2nd fighters pass that just teases them would have been enough to calm people who were upset about Byleth down.
